						<summary>

						<p>On a broken pillar lying behind the Veṅkatēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Matsya: Vallabharāja.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1385 <hi rend="italic">(Śara-nāga-Viśva),</hi> Svabhānu, Jyēshṭha, Pūrṇimā, Thursday, corresponding to 1463 A.D., June 16.</p>						

						<p>Records the performance of an Agnishṭōma sacrifice, as per the injunctions of the Śāstras, by the king on the bank of the river Danta.</p>						

						</summary>
